sec.p:
Ned returns to the Leftorium to work on his taxes and to take his mind off things. Here he meets a beautiful woman (voiced by
Marisa Tomei
), who is after a pair of left-handed eyelash curlers. After chatting to Ned, she eventually asks him out on a date. Later, after the mysterious shopper has gone, Ned spots a movie poster with the woman's face on it; she is a movie star, Sara Sloane (who once dated Rainier Wolfcastle but broke up with him because of the way he spoke).
